CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 9, 1964, pg. 1 reads:" World-Wide Delegation - The nearly 900 delegates attending the Methodist General Conference in Pittsburgh is world-wide, representing many races that inhabit the globe. The Courier cameraman captured some of these in above pictures...Fourth Photo: Rev. Earl Cunningham, Nashville and Rev. Ernest T. Dixon Sr., West Texas Conference.....-Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Reverend Earl Cunningham and Reverend Ernest T. Dixon Sr., standing in interior during 1964 United Methodist Church General Conference
